quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
35,12,"The two masses of water are not alike. {1} The one is sweet, sates thirst, and is pleasant to drink from, while the other is salt, bitter on the tongue. Yet from both you eat fresh meat, {2} and extract from it ornaments that you wear; {3} and you see ships cruising through it that you may seek of His Bounty and be thankful to Him.",footnotes:1:That is
35,13,"He causes the night to phase into the day and the day into the night, {1} and He has subjected the sun and the moon, each running its course to an appointed term. {2} That is Allah, your Lord; to Him belongs the Kingdom; but those whom you call upon, apart from Allah, possess not so much as the skin of a date-stone. {3}",footnotes:1:That is
35,14,"If you call upon them, they cannot hear your prayer. And if they hear it, they cannot answer it. {1} On the Day of Resurrection they will disown you for associating others with Allah in His Divinity. {2} No one can inform you of the truth save the All-Aware. {3}",footnotes:1:This does not mean that they cannot tell aloud
35,15,"O people, it is you who stand in need of Allah; {1} as for Allah, He is Self-Sufficient, Immensely Praiseworthy. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
35,16,"If He wishes, He can remove you and put in your place a new creation."
35,17,"That surely is not difficult for Allah. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
35,18,"No one can bear another's burden. {1} If a heavily laden one should call another to carry his load, none of it shall be carried by the other, even though he be a near of kin. {2} (O Prophet), you can warn only those who fear their Lord without seeing Him and establish Prayer. {3} Whoever purifies himself does so to his own good. To Allah is the final return.",footnotes:1:“Burden”: the burden of the responsibilities of actions. It means: In the sight of Allah every one is responsible for his own actions and for no one else’s. There is no possibility that Allah will place the burden of one man’s responsibility upon the other
